In [[Japanese mythology]], {{Nihongo||国産み|'''Kuniumi'''|extra=literally "birth or formation of the country"}} is the traditional and legendary history of the emergence of the [[Japanese archipelago]], of islands, as narrated in the [[Kojiki]] and [[Nihon Shoki]]. According to this legend, after the creation of Heaven and Earth, the [[kami|gods]] [[Izanagi]] and [[Izanami]] were given the task of forming a series of islands that would become what is now Japan. In Japanese mythology, these islands make up the known world. The creation of Japan is followed by the creation of the gods (''[[kamiumi]]'').

